import pandas as pd
import os 
datasets_paths = [os.path.join('Order_Book_Data', i) for i in os.listdir('Order_Book_Data')]
import os
import pandas as pd

data_dict = {}

for path in datasets_paths:
    filename = os.path.splitext(os.path.basename(path))[0]  # get filename without extension
    key = filename[:]  # last 5 characters
    data_dict[key] = pd.read_parquet(path)

keylist = list(data_dict.keys())

def compute_midpoint(snapshot: pd.DataFrame) -> float:
    best_bid = snapshot.loc[snapshot['Side'] == 'bid', 'Price'].max()
    best_ask = snapshot.loc[snapshot['Side'] == 'ask', 'Price'].min()
    if pd.isna(best_bid) or pd.isna(best_ask):
        return float('nan')
    return (best_bid + best_ask) / 2
def compute_vwap(snapshot: pd.DataFrame, pct_band=0.2) -> float:
    midpoint = compute_midpoint(snapshot)
    if pd.isna(midpoint):
        return float('nan')
    lower = midpoint * (1 - pct_band)
    upper = midpoint * (1 + pct_band)
    clipped = snapshot[(snapshot['Price'] >= lower) & (snapshot['Price'] <= upper)]
    if clipped.empty:
        return float('nan')
    total_value = (clipped['Price'] * clipped['Size']).sum()
    total_volume = clipped['Size'].sum()
    return total_value / total_volume


def get_best_bid(snapshot: pd.DataFrame) -> float:
    bids = snapshot[snapshot['Side'] == 'bid']
    return bids['Price'].max() if not bids.empty else float('nan')
def get_best_ask(snapshot: pd.DataFrame) -> float:
    asks = snapshot[snapshot['Side'] == 'ask']
    return asks['Price'].min() if not asks.empty else float('nan')
def get_best_bid_ask(snapshot: pd.DataFrame) -> tuple[float, float]:
    return get_best_bid(snapshot), get_best_ask(snapshot)
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.dates as mdates

def plot_orderbook_timeseries(data_dict, key):
    X = data_dict[key]
    mid, vwap, ask, bid, dates = [], [], [], [], []
    
    for Timestamp, data in X.groupby('Timestamp'):
        mid.append(compute_midpoint(data))
        vwap.append(compute_vwap(data))
        ask.append(get_best_ask(data))
        bid.append(get_best_bid(data))
        dates.append(Timestamp)

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 5))

    ax.plot(dates, bid, label='Best Bid')
    ax.plot(dates, ask, label='Best Ask')
    # ax.plot(dates, mid, label='Midpoint', linestyle='--')
    # ax.plot(dates, vwap, label='VWAP', linestyle=':')

    ax.set_title(key.replace('_', ' '), fontsize=14)
    ax.set_xlabel('Timestamp', fontsize=12)
    ax.set_ylabel('Price', fontsize=12)

    ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M'))
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(mdates.AutoDateLocator())

    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    ax.legend()
    ax.grid(True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.5)

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()



import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.dates as mdates

def plot_orderbook_subplots(data_dict, keylist, start, end):
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(3, 2, figsize=(20, 14), sharex=False)
    axes = axes.flatten()
    for i, key in enumerate(keylist[-6:]):
        X = data_dict[key]
        mid, vwap, ask, bid, dates = [], [], [], [], []
        Z = X[X.Timestamp >= start]
        Z = Z[Z.Timestamp <= end]

        for Timestamp, data in Z.groupby('Timestamp'):
            mid.append(compute_midpoint(data))
            vwap.append(compute_vwap(data))
            ask.append(get_best_ask(data))
            bid.append(get_best_bid(data))
            dates.append(Timestamp)

        ax = axes[i]
        ax.plot(dates, bid, label='Bid', lw =3)
        ax.plot(dates, ask, label='Ask', lw =3)
        ax.plot(dates, mid, label='Mid', linestyle='--', lw =3)
        ax.plot(dates, vwap, label='VWAP', linestyle=':', lw =3)

        ax.set_title(key.replace('_', ' '), fontsize = 20)
        ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%m-%d %H:%M'))
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(mdates.AutoDateLocator())
        ax.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
        ax.grid(True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.5)

        if i == 0:
            ax.legend(fontsize=14)
    
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

# Chunk 2: Plot the standing order book and overlay belief curve B(p) from VI parameters

# Select market index and number of snapshots to plot
# Choose market and number of snapshots to show
market_idx = 3
num_snapshots = 10

# Parse timestamps as datetime
vi_times = pd.to_datetime(vi_outputs[market_idx]['timestamp'].unique())
book_times = pd.to_datetime(orderbooks[market_idx]['Timestamp'].unique())

# Get sorted intersection of valid times
valid_times = sorted(set(vi_times) & set(book_times))

step = 2
start = int(step*num_snapshots)
# Take the last N
selected_times = valid_times[-start::step]

for timer in selected_times:
    # (your full plotting code here, replacing `snapshot_idx = -5`)

    # Extract relevant data
    df_vi = vi_outputs[market_idx]
    df_vi.timestamp = pd.to_datetime(df_vi.timestamp)
    # timer = df_vi.timestamp.unique()[snapshot_idx]
    df_vi = df_vi[df_vi.timestamp == timer]


    df_book = orderbooks[market_idx]
    df_book = df_book[df_book.Timestamp == timer]

    # Compute B(p) belief curve
    mu = df_vi['mu'].values[0]
    nu = df_vi['nu'].values[0]
    a = mu * nu
    b = (1 - mu) * nu

    p_grid = np.linspace(0, 1, 500)
    B_p = beta.cdf(p_grid, a, b)

    # Plotting the order book
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(16, 10))
    gs = fig.add_gridspec(2, 2, height_ratios=[1, 2])

    top_ax = fig.add_subplot(gs[0, :])         # Top plot spans both columns
    axs = [fig.add_subplot(gs[1, 0]),          # Bottom left
        fig.add_subplot(gs[1, 1])]          # Bottom right

    vwap, midpoint = compute_vwap(df_book), compute_midpoint(df_book)



    # top plot 

    plotdf = orderbooks[market_idx]
    plotdf.Timestamp = pd.to_datetime(plotdf.Timestamp)

    mid, vwap_total, ask, bid, dates = [], [], [], [], []

    for Timestamp, data in plotdf.groupby('Timestamp'):
        mid.append(compute_midpoint(data))
        vwap_total.append(compute_vwap(data))
        ask.append(get_best_ask(data))
        bid.append(get_best_bid(data))
        dates.append(Timestamp)

    # Plot time series of bid/ask/mid/VWAP
    top_ax.plot(dates, bid, label="Best Bid", color="blue")
    top_ax.plot(dates, ask, label="Best Ask", color="orange")
    top_ax.plot(dates, mid, label="Midpoint", color="purple", linestyle="--")
    top_ax.plot(dates, vwap_total, label="VWAP", color="black", linestyle=":")

    top_ax.axvline(pd.to_datetime(timer), color="red", linestyle="--", label="Selected Snapshot")

    top_ax.set_title("Order Book Price Summary Over Time", fontsize=16)
    top_ax.set_ylabel("Price", fontsize=14)
    top_ax.tick_params(labelsize=12)
    top_ax.legend(fontsize=12)


    # Standing volume
    bids = df_book[df_book['Side'] == 'bid']
    bids = bids[bids.Price > bids.Price.max()-.2]
    asks = df_book[df_book['Side'] == 'ask']
    asks = asks[asks.Price < asks.Price.min()+.2]
    axs[0].bar(bids['Price'], bids['Size'], width=0.005, label='Bid', color='blue')
    axs[0].bar(asks['Price'], asks['Size'], width=0.005, label='Ask', color='orange')
    axs[0].axvline(midpoint, color='purple', linestyle='--', label='Midprice', lw = 2)
    axs[0].axvline(vwap, color='black', linestyle=':', label='VWAP', lw = 2)
    axs[0].axvline(mu, color='red', linestyle='--', label="Mean belief (μ)", lw = 2)
    axs[0].set_title("Standing Order Book Snapshot", fontsize=16)
    axs[0].set_xlabel("Price", fontsize=14)
    axs[0].set_ylabel("Size", fontsize=14)
    axs[0].tick_params(labelsize=12)
    axs[0].legend(fontsize=12)

    # Belief distribution
    axs[1].plot(p_grid, B_p, color='green', label=f"B(p)\nμ={mu:.2f}, ν={nu:.2f}", lw = 2)
    axs[1].axvline(mu, color='red', linestyle='--', label="Mean belief (μ)", lw = 2)
    axs[1].axvline(midpoint, color='purple', linestyle='--', label='Midprice', lw = 2)
    axs[1].axvline(vwap, color='black', linestyle=':', label='VWAP', lw = 2)
    axs[1].set_title("Estimated Belief Distribution", fontsize=16)
    axs[1].set_xlabel("Price p", fontsize=14)
    axs[1].set_ylabel("B(p)", fontsize=14)
    axs[1].tick_params(labelsize=12)
    axs[1].legend(fontsize=12)
    fig.suptitle(f"Market {orderbook_paths[market_idx].replace('_',' ').split('OBR')[1].split('.csv')[0]}", fontsize=18)
    # plt.tight_layout(rect=[0, 0.03, 1, 0.95])  # leaves room for suptitle

    # plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
